1. docker pull <image_name>:
command is used to download a Docker image from a registry (such as Docker Hub) to your local machine.

2. docker images:
command is used to list the Docker images that are available on your local system.

3. docker run <image_name>:
command is used to create and start a new container from a specified Docker image.

4. docker run -it <image_name> (-it -> interact)
is used to start a new Docker container and interact with it via a terminal.

5. docker ps -a 
command is used to list all containers on your system, regardless of their current state.

6. docker ps
command is used to list all containers that is on running state.

7. docker start container_name/container_ID
command is used to restart a container that is currently in a stopped state.

8. docker stop container_name 
command is used to stop a container that is currently in a running state.

9. docker rmi image_name/image_id
is used to remove one or more Docker images

10. docker rm <container_name_or_id>
is used to remove remove a container

